from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
scaler = StandardScaler()
df = pd.read_csv("valeursfoncieres-2021.txt", sep="|", low_memory = False)
df=df[["Date mutation","Valeur fonciere","Surface terrain"]]
df['Date mutation'] = df['Date mutation'].str.replace('/','')
pd.to_numeric(df['Date mutation'], errors='coerce')
df['Valeur fonciere'] = df['Valeur fonciere'].str.replace(',','.')
pd.to_numeric(df['Valeur fonciere'], errors='coerce')
df_full=pd.DataFrame(scaler.fit_transform(df))
df_full=df_full.dropna()
acp=PCA(n_components=2)
df_full=acp.fit_transform(df_full)
print('Les composantes: ',acp.components_)
print(acp.explained_variance_ratio_)
tot_exp=round(acp.explained_variance_ratio_.sum(),6)
print('Cette acp permet de expliquer ',tot_exp,' des données' )
plt.bar(np.arange(len(acp.explained_variance_ratio_)), acp.explained_variance_ratio_,)
plt.ylim(0,1)
plt.title("Variance expliquée")

import sklearn.metrics as sm
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from yellowbrick.cluster import KElbowVisualizer


distortions = []
K = range(1,10)
for k in K:
    kmeanModel = KMeans(n_clusters=k, init = 'k-means++', random_state = 42)
    kmeanModel.fit(df_full)
    distortions.append(kmeanModel.inertia_)
    
plt.figure(figsize=(16,8))
plt.plot(K, distortions, 'bx-')
visualizer = KElbowVisualizer(kmeanModel, k=K, locate_elbow=True)

visualizer.fit(df_full)  
visualizer.show()
